{"ID":270370, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"370\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs369.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs371.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 370<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">secret, they cry&mdash;&ldquo;The Prophet says there are many Gods, and this proves that he has fallen.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">It has been my intention for a long time to take up this subject and lay it clearly before the\n  people, and show what my faith is in relation to this interesting matter. I have contemplated the\n  saying of Jesus (Luke 17th chapter, 26th verse)&mdash;&ldquo;And as it was in the days of Noah, so shall it\n  be also in the days of the Son of Man.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> And if it does rain, I&rsquo;ll preach this doctrine, for the truth\n  shall be preached.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Plurality of Gods<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">I will preach on the plurality of Gods.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> I have selected this text for that express purpose. I wish\n  to declare I have always and in all congregations when I have preached on the subject of the Deity,\n  it has been the plurality of Gods. It has been preached by the Elders for fifteen years.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I have always declared God to be a distinct personage, Jesus Christ a separate and distinct\n  personage from God the Father, and the Holy Ghost was a distinct personage and a Spirit: and these\n  three constitute three distinct personages<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and three Gods. If this is in accordance with the New\n  Testament, lo and behold!  we have three Gods anyhow, and they are plural; and who can contradict\n  it?<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Our text says, &ldquo;And hath made us kings and priests unto God and His Father.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> The Apostles\n  have discovered that there were Gods above, for Paul says God was the Father of our Lord Jesus\n  Christ.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> My object was to preach the scriptures,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and preach the doctrine they contain, there being\n  a God above,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ. I am bold to declare I have taught all the strong\n  doctrines publicly,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and always teach stronger doctrines in public than in private.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">John was one of the men, and apostles declare they were made kings and priests unto God,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> the\n  Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> It reads just so in the Revelation, Hence the doctrine of a plurality\n  of Gods is as prominent in the Bible as any other doctrine. It is all over the face of the Bible. It\n  stands beyond the power of controversy. A wayfaring man,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> though a fool, need not err therein.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Paul says there are Gods many and Lords many.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> I want to set it forth in a plain and simple\n  manner; but to us there is but one God<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span>&mdash;that is <i>pertaining to us;<\/i> and he is in all and<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109087\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109087)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109087)\">Acts 13:6<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111632\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111632)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111632)\">Mosiah 15:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112503\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112503)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112503)\">Hel. 13:26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108553\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108553)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108553)\">Luke 17:26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112322\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112322)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112322)\">Alma 43:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113322\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113322)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113322)\">D&amp;C 19:37<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113969\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113969)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113969)\">D&amp;C 50:17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115775\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115775)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115775)\">D&amp;C 121:28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116278\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116278)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116278)\">D&amp;C 130:22<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117178\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117178)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117178)\">A of F 1:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110672\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110672)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110672)\">Rev. 1:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109393\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109393)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109393)\">Rom. 15:6<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109624\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109624)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109624)\">2 Cor. 1:3<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109687\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109687)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109687)\">2 Cor. 11:31<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109758\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109758)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109758)\">Eph. 1:3<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109884\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109884)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109884)\">Col. 1:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109048\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109048)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109048)\">Acts 8:35<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106836\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106836)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106836)\">Ps. 108:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108342\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108342)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108342)\">Mark 8:32-33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108882\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108882)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108882)\">John 18:20-21<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108701\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108701)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108701)\">John 6:59-69<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110673\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110673)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110673)\">Rev. 1:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109625\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109625)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109625)\">2 Cor. 1:3<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110894\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110894)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110894)\">Rev. 22:21<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107157\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107157)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107157)\">Isa. 35:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109477\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109477)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109477)\">1 Cor. 8:5-6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116728\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116728)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116728)\">Moses 1:20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}